    Decouple auth from MeetMind: rename MEETMIND_ORIGIN -> AUTH_ORIGIN
    
    Follow-up to PR #28. The user clarified that LIVE's tokens
    DON'T come from MeetMind — they come from whichever parent issues
    tokens to MeetMind too. So 'MeetMind' was the wrong word in three
    places: the env var, the const, and the user-facing copy. The SSO
    LOGIC stays identical to speech-to-text, but the wiring is now
    parent-agnostic.
    
    What changed
    - VITE_AUTH_ORIGIN is now the primary env var. VITE_MEETMIND_ORIGIN
      remains as a back-compat fallback so any Render/Vercel configs
      that already set it keep working without re-deploys.
    - Default origin changed from 'https://meetmind.vercel.app' to ''.
      An unconfigured production build now stays unauthenticated rather
      than silently trusting a third party. The strict origin check
      rejects every postMessage when AUTH_ORIGIN is empty.
    - The postMessage listener is no longer attached at all when
      AUTH_ORIGIN is empty — saves a no-op listener on every message
      that flies past the window in development. A dev-only
      console.info hint tells the engineer how to fix it.
    - All user-visible 'MeetMind' strings replaced with parent-agnostic
      copy:
        'Sign in via MeetMind to view your saved meetings' -> 'Sign in
        to view your saved meetings'
        placeholder body 'Open the LIVE Translator from inside MeetMind'
        -> 'Open this app from your authenticated host'
    - The literal postMessage type string 'MEETMIND_AUTH' is preserved
      as the discriminator. That keeps LIVE drop-in compatible with the
      same parent that already speaks the speech-to-text contract — only
      the parent's domain needs to be configured per app.
    - New exported helper getAuthOrigin() so the UI can show the
      configured origin in tooltips/diagnostics if useful later.
    
    What stayed
    - Comments referencing 'MeetMind' that describe the historical
      origin of the persistence code (port of the old MeetMind server.js)
      are factually correct and preserved.
    - The MEETMIND_AUTH message-type literal is preserved for
      cross-app contract compatibility.
    - All four authFetch wiring + the SignInPlaceholder card unchanged
      in behaviour.
    
    Build clean: 251 kB JS / 77 kB gzipped — no size change.

